Hey friends, it's time for a life update! You may not know this, but I've been a full-time communication instructor at OSU since 2014. I used to teach in the classroom, but now I've designed a course called "Communicating Online” that I’ve been teaching for the last 5 years, along with others like public speaking and social media etc.. It's been amazing to be a part of OSU's top 10 best online college program for years.

But that's not all, over the past two months I've been diving back into scholarly research and writing a paper about political visual communication on Facebook. And guess what? My paper got accepted for presentation at the Northwest Communication Association conference in Couer D'alene, Idaho! I'm so excited to share my research and hear from others in the field.

This job has been an incredible blessing. I’ll never forget this one day in particular in 2012 when I was praying, fasting and crying out to God during a difficult season of my life. The next day, God provided the beginning to the process of becoming an instructor. I truly believe God opened up this opportunity for me as a blessing and for provision, and it happened in an unbelievable, miraculously clear way. I’d love to share the story in detail sometime because all the glory goes to God! It’s been a challenging and fun job, and I'm grateful for the department of professors I work with. When we make the Lord our refuge, He is always faithful to provide and deliver.

In times of tragedy, it's common for people to dismiss prayer and Jesus as ineffective solutions. But let's not forget that prayer is powerful and effective, with numerous verses in the Bible emphasizing the importance of constantly praying for our protection, loved ones, church, children, nation, and leaders. Prayer is as important as breathing. As we face the challenges of this world, we must remember that our battles are not only physical but also spiritual, and prayer is essential in fighting against the dark forces that seek to harm and divide us.

To bring about meaningful change, we must start with our own hearts. We must humbly submit to Jesus and seek His face, for He will guide us on what to do and say, and how to bring glory to Him. Let's prioritize our personal relationship with Him, so we can be agents of positive change in the world. We want to do things that are backed by God’s strength and power.

“For our struggle is not against flesh and blood, but against the rulers, against the authorities, against the powers of this dark world and against the spiritual forces of evil in the heavenly realms.” Ephesians 6:12

My main focus this month is balance. I just got done with my busy wedding season. Classes have started up at the university where I teach full-time. I’ve had a lot of collabs recently. Engagement and family photoshoots have begun, and I’ve been serving at my church. Here are some practical steps of how I balance it all. I like to start my day with the Lord in prayer and reading my Bible as this puts me at peace as I move through my busy schedule. 

I’ve found that when I seek God before everything else I feel less overwhelmed by the things that I need to do. I usually begin my time with praying and thanking Him for whatever comes to mind. Next, I like to ask God what I need to work on in my own life while also asking for his forgiveness and help in my shortcomings. After that I begin to pray for other people and the world. Then, I end with asking God to help me with my tasks for that day along with any other heavy burdens I’m facing or am worried about.

As I read the scriptures I learn more about our God. I see how He shows up in different people’s lives in the Bible and I feel like I always see a new side of his personality when I’m reading these stories. The wisdom within the word is unmatched. Samuel 1 & 2 are my favorite books in the Bible! I’ve noticed a big difference when I begin my day with reading the word and I always feel so much balance and peace when I commit each day to the Lord 🫶🏻

I can’t believe I’m saying this, but recently I was attacked by an owl 🦉 I had no idea that owls sometimes “dive-bomb” human’s heads (yes that’s the official term). When I called the department of fish and wildlife they were shocked because it almost never happens in the city and is very very rare. After the attack I did a lot of research and learned a lot about these birds. The species that attacked is called a brown Great Horned Owl, also known as a Tiger Owl, and has a wingspan just under 5ft. Their talons are very sharp and they are territorial species, so I must have been in its territory as I walked under the branch it was perched on. I’ve honestly had a little fear of birds my whole life so to have this happen was unfortunate, but it could have been worse. Thankfully it didn’t get my face or scratch me up too badly. There’s more to the story but I had to edit this down to 1min. 30 sec. for instagram. All I want to communicate is to watch out for those owls! If you see one, don’t try and take a pic or get too close to it!! They are beautiful from a distance, but if you get too close they might attack and dive-bomb your head!

Hello November! This pumpkin was harvested because it was planted several months prior. With Thanksgiving just around the corner, it made me think about the Bible verse that says “you reap what you sow” Galatians 6:7-9. It’s good to evaluate what we are sowing with our lives and our time, because eventually we will begin to see the fruit of it in our lives. The Bible says that the fruit of the spirit are love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, gentleness, faithfulness and self-control. Unfortunately, there will be moments when we see the opposite produced in our lives such as hate, depression, anxiety, impatience, disrespectful, evilness, harshness, doubt, and lack of self-control. In these moments it’s important not to feel shame, but to allow the conviction to make us reassess what we are “sowing” in our lives and make a change.  May the peace of God be with you in this season and by his strength I pray that you’ll reap a beautiful harvest of godly fruit this year 🍂🫶🏻✨🙏🏼

While I was pulling into the gas station today a young kid who was working pretended to jump in front of my car and then started laughing. I laughed too, not sure why because it was actually kind of annoying haha. Then he came up to my window to pump the gas. I asked him how he was doing and he said, “alright” with a downcast face. “I would be doing better if I would have actually jumped in front of your car and died,” and he laughed again. Gut punch. Did I just hear what I thought I heard?? I mirrored his emotions and laughed again… I wish I didn’t laugh when I don’t know what to say. As he was pumping my gas I almost started crying in compassion and thought of the verse, “out of the overflow of the heart the mouth speaks.” I knew this kid was struggling and I knew I wasn’t there by accident. I knew what I was called to do. Fear sunk in. What if he thinks I’m weird! What if I say it wrong? The kid came back. “Hey!” I said. “God has an amazing plan for your life. One filled with joy and purpose. Following God is so exciting and I think God sent me here to tell you he loves you.” “I haven’t been to church in a while,” he said. I responded, “God is everywhere, he’s even here right now. He’s even in your thoughts. You can talk to God right here while you’re working and he hears you. I’ll be praying for you, Miguel, and I’m excited for his plans for your life. God loves you!” I drove off, almost shaking, but knowing that God’s power was at work in this kid’s life today. I pray that this story encourages you, that if God can speak through someone like me, scared and unsure of what to say, he can speak through you too! All you have to do is open your mouth and let the Lord speak through you 🗣️🫶🏻

Daily dose of encouragement from the Bible: “Be on your guard; stand firm in the faith; be courageous; be strong. Do everything in love.” 1 Corinthians 16:13 If we filtered everything we did through the directions in this verse, we’d be in good place. Here are some questions that you can ask yourself today that will help put you on a good path- 

Am I watchful and alert to the ways that the enemy might be hurting my walk with God (ex. pride, sin, division, selfishness, bad theology etc.)? 

Am I earnestly seeking the Lord and believing in faith that what he says is true? Do I need to pray and ask God for more faith?

Am I courageous in my faith, able to talk to others about him and stand up for what the Bible says?

Am I filled with the Holy Spirit? Because our flesh is weak, but the spirit within us is strong!

Do I truly understand what love is? Are my actions (whether well received or not) being done out of my love for the other person?

Be encouraged that God cares about your life and is helping you every step of the way!

Welcome to the little fairytale town of Kandern, Germany! From the cobblestone streets and multicolored buildings to the fall foliage and cute cafés… every corner of this city is beautiful! But the greatest gift of all is the time spent with my family in this part of the world 🇩🇪✨🫶🏻

Found the Christmas store of my dreams in Germany! Every corner kept getting better and more extravagant! I felt like I was in Santa’s workshop from the Santa Clause movie 🎄✨❤️ @kaethe_wohlfahrt @rothenburgtourism

Rothenburg, Germany circa 2023 📸 This city is a part of the popular “Romantic Road” of medieval towns. Right when I thought Germany couldn’t get any cuter, this city took my breath away with its beauty and charm! Can’t wait to go back again someday, and maybe visit all the towns on this Romantic Road journey 🖤❤️💛

If you ever visit Rothenburg ob der Tauber I’ve got your itinerary planned for the day!! First begin by parking at the the Gallows Gate (Galgentor) and start your day by walking through the tower built in 1600! Next make your way to Plönlein, the iconic photo spot in the city. After that grab yourself a pretzel from one of the many bakeries. Then head up the Town Hall Tower for a wide angle view of Rothenburg and surrounding. Unfortunately, it was closed when I went, but it looked awesome! After than grab lunch because all the little shops close for lunch break, ha! After that explore all the fun little shops and cobblestone alleyways. Check out St.Jakobs church and the Käthe Wohlfarht year-round Christmas store that are right next to each other. I was seriously blown away by the whimsical experience of the Christmas store!! Then go climb into one of the many entrances to the wall around the city. It’s Germany’s best-preserved walled city and is something you don’t want to miss! After that grab an iconic Schneeball, snowball in English, which is a deep-fried pastry that you just have to try while you’re there. Everyone sells them! End your day with a fun dinner anywhere in the city! 😊

I grew up in a family where love wasn’t confusing. I never had to wonder if my parents loved each other or us kids. I never wondered if a fight would turn into a divorce. I never saw someone withholding love or playing games to try and get the other person’s attention (maybe why I don’t understand or play love games in dating myself haha). In my family, love was rather simple. We love because God first loved us. Period. We care for and help each other, because God cares for and helps us. We are committed to each other, because God is committed to us. We love unconditionally, because that’s how God loves us. We admit our wrongs, have hard conversations with each other, and sometimes speak hard truth with love as the motivator. I’m not saying my family is perfect. We’re actually all imperfect and sinful people who argue sometimes and desperately need a savior. We all have big and small problems from time to time, but I’d be lying if I said I didn’t understand the huge blessing I’ve had with the family I have but don’t deserve. God and his word has been the firm foundation, established by my parents, that our family has grown upon. I’m writing this to encourage anyone who’s grown up in houses where love was confusing, awkward, painful, embarrassing, withheld, uncertain or unstable. Have courage, brave soul. You can be the difference for your future family. God is for you and will bring you a loving family that is different than how you grew up or what you experienced if you trust him to lead you to and through it! If you’re already in a family that isn’t loving and it seems hopeless, put your hope in God because God has the power to change it! He can restore, rebuild or renew even the worst situations that seem hopeless. If you call yourself a Christian, you are my brother and sister in Christ and we have a perfect example of a loving father that will help us in all situations, Jesus Christ!! God loves you and is rooting for you, and so am I!! Happy Thanksgiving! 🤎🍂🫶🏻🍁

I just love what Christmas brings out of many people around the world - a season of joy, lit up houses in the midst of darkness, hope, thoughtful generosity, good food, coziness, anticipation, hosting with love, community events, thankfulness, and a constant reminder of Jesus’ birth. No other holiday brings out the goodness that I see in Christmas, and I believe it’s because this day is so much more than just a holiday! The ways we celebrate are just reflections of what God brought to the world through His son. Jesus was the most joyful person to ever walk the earth, he was the light to our dark world, he so loved the world that he gave the ultimate gift of salvation and his own life, he loved a good dinner with friends, he was peace, he brought anticipation for his return, he was love without budging on the truth everywhere he went, he attended many community events (including the church almost daily) and loved people and loved God, he was the most thankful man that’s ever existed, and he came as a baby, and He was King from birth. I love how we take a whole 1-2 months to celebrate Jesus! And in Jesus-like fashion, our celebrations and traditions for Him are also blessings in our lives. Even people who don’t know or believe in Jesus are blessed by Christmas. That’s so like Jesus and I love Him! I pray that the spirit of Christmas, God’s spirit, would continue throughout the year in our joy, thoughtful generosity, hosting and worship to our King! He is worthy 👑🐑🕯️🕊️🎄❤️

The New Year is finally here!! It’s another year of our Lord, sustained by Him and Him alone 🙌🏼 I love reading everyone’s goals, and I have a few myself that I’m looking forward to working on! However, our goals are meaningless if God is not in them. It’s easy to create goals for different categories like health, relational, and spiritual… but the reality is that all goals are spiritual for the person who has made God their Lord and savior! God wants to partner with us to accomplish the goals and dreams he’s given us. He’s a relational God who loves to help and give us supernatural strength!

Back in 2010 during Christmas break from college I prayed and asked God for a hobby. Right after I prayed I suddenly had this desire to buy a camera (it felt so random), but God has honored that faithful step. He’s blessed me and he’s blessed others through my skill. He even showed me a real life miracle in making a lighting bolt strike down at a wedding the instant I prayed and asked him for one. He helped me get that photo! Imagine if I never bought the camera or prayed the prayer for the lightning bolt. God honors faith and resilience.

I want to extend the invitation to join me in setting aside some time alone with God to ask him to help us plan for the year. Maybe he’ll tell you to faithfully step away from something, or step further into something you already have, or maybe you’ll suddenly have a new desire after you pray. 

If God puts a dream in your heart, put it in good soil so that it can grow! Give it lots of prayer and ask for God’s supernatural strength. Then take a faithful leap towards the dream in your heart. 

“Take delight in the Lord, and he will give you the desires of your heart.” Psalm 37:4

To take delight in the Lord basically means to find great joy in his presence. Delighting in someone only happens when we know them well, and when we have been a faithful friend. To delight in the Lord we must get to know him better and be faithful to him. Here’s to honoring the dream God’s put in your heart and watching it grow through the power of his Holy Spirit that is alive in us 🫶🏻🎊
